@bearmatthews Well, I started my "career" as a university drop-out in the mid-'90s. I discovered this cool thing called the Internet when I was at university, and it distracted me from studying so much that I failed my exams and got kicked out! I started working as a tech support guy at an ISP, and ended up as CTO of a startup when the Dot-Com bubble burst and we had to shut down in the summer of 2000 (see https://jackgavigan.com/2011/01/21/zedzed-com-an-obituary/). 

I ended up taking a 3-month contract installing web servers for an investment bank to pay the rent until the Dot-Com sector recovered but it took longer than expected, and I ended up working for banks for the next 8 years, including a stint as a trader. After the credit crunch, I became a freelance project/product manager (still working mostly for banks) doing 3/6-month contracts, working about 50% of the year, and doing startup-related stuff the rest of the time. I co-founded a startup with some of the folks who built Retroshare.cc but nobody was interested in decentralized/peer-to-peer technology at the time so we failed to raise any money. I spent some time in Silicon Valley, and started LDN2SFO to help introduce other entrepreneurs from the UK to the eco-system there. 

I got interested in the whole cryptocurrency / blockchain technology space, and ended up as an advisor to the company behind Zcash. Then Zooko asked me to join the company shortly before Zcash launched, in late 2016, and I've been there since. 😃
Great stuff!! It's been awesome to watch the developments as Zcash had a strong 6-month climb (minus the slight recent slip)

Hi. I'm Michael. I'm the founder of Freshpaint, a YC backed startup. To make a long story short, after finishing high school in 2015, I immediately started working at a startup. During my time there, I was the main person who worked on scaling their Postgres cluster with 100s of TBs of data. I also led multiple projects that each resulted in a seven figure cost savings. That work earned me the nickname "Michael Margins".

During my last year there, I lead the database team, the team responsible for managing their database cluster. I left in April 2019 to work on a side project. I was able to get into the YC S2019 batch with my project. What we were initially working on didn't work out and we wound up pivoting the business to Freshpaint (https://www.freshpaint.io/). You can think of it as "low-code Segment". We let you send data to any marketing and analytics tool without writing code. Instead you use our point and click interface to specify an element of your site, say the login button, and you can specify that whenever someone clicks that button, that is considered a "login" event in Google Analytics. This let's you get data from your website into other tools in minutes instead of months.

We just raised a $1.5M seed round a few months ago which you can read about here: https://www.freshpaint.io/blog/anatomy-of-a-seed-round-during-covid-19

I'm happy to be here and hope I get to meet you all!
